title: China and the Philippines trade blame over South China Sea clash
description: The latest incident comes amid ongoing tensions between China and the Philippines over the disputed strategic waterway.

title: Small plane crashes into San Diego neighbourhood, setting over 10 homes on fire
description: Authorities say multiple homes have been hit, causing a gigantic debris field in the Californian neighbourhood

title: RBA deputy says China knew it had a strong hand in trade war with US
description: RBA deputy governor Andrew Hauser says he witnessed first-hand Chinas willingness to fight a US trade war.

title: What we know about young couple shot dead outside Jewish museum in Washington DC
description: Israel has identified the two victims, who were a young couple, and the suspect will be interrogated on Thursday morning.

title: NT minister references Darwinism, quotes Nazi leader in anti-racism debate
description: The Northern Territorys multicultural affairs minister has defended referencing Charles Darwins theory of evolution and quoting Hitlers propaganda chief during a parliamentary debate about racism.

title: Who are Kneecap and why has a member been charged with terrorism?
description: British police have charged Liam OHanna, a member of the Irish rap group Kneecap, with a terrorism offence for allegedly waving a flag in support of Hezbollah at a concert in London. How did we get here?

title: AMA warns severe flu season ahead, as Qld cases surge by 36 per cent
description: Flu infections across the state are already 36 per cent higher than this time last year and health authorities are warning of a tough winter ahead.

title: NBL superstar Bryce Cotton set to sign with 36ers
description: The Adelaide 36rs are set to announce a momentous signing, with NBL superstar and five-time MVP Bryce Cotton expected to join the club.

title: Dolphins defy atrocious conditions to smash Bulldogs in 36-point rout
description: The wind and the rain were meant to keep scores low but the Dolphins defied the odds to record the second-biggest win in their history against ladder-leaders Canterbury.

title: Significant sums Misuse of public money claims referred for NT probe
description: The NT opposition leader has referred serious misuse of public money allegations at the Darwin Waterfront Corporation to a parliamentary committee.

title: Rio Tinto chief executive Jakob Stausholm steps down
description: Mining giant Rio Tinto has announced chief executive Jakob Stausholm will step down, more than four years since he took over following global criticism of the company for its destruction of ancient rock shelters in WA.

title: Father of Sandipan Dhar says Joondalup hospital destroyed their lives
description: A coronial inquest into the death of a toddler at a Perth hospital has ended with emotional testimony from the boys father, who says his family had been betrayed.

title: Hopefully we see them in September Smith already eyeing rematch after close win
description: Bailey Smith said he probably wouldnt have played in the Cats close win over the Dogs if it wasnt against his old side as hes battling a shin injury.

title: Deeply frustrating Calls to end three-year delay on CSIRO land sale
description: Once used for agricultural research, the development of the CSIRO Ginninderra Experiment Station, a 701-hectare area of land between Belconnen and the Barton Highway, was first floated a decade ago.

title: Theyre a lost cause Messages about in-laws shown in mushroom trial
description: Erin Patterson wanted nothing to do with her extended family, according to online messages allegedly sent eight months before the fatal lunch at her home.

title: Domestic violence lecturer wont train police as controversial interview reviewed
description: A university lecturer who teaches Tasmanian police recruits about domestic violence will not be involved in police training courses while comments she made in an interview with controversial mens rights commentator Bettina Arndt are reviewed.

title: Ex-surf coach pleads guilty to child sex charges involving eight victims
description: The 28 charges against Connor John Christopher Lyons include indecent treatment of children and making child exploitation material.

title: Organisers say new sports for Brisbane Olympics need to be realistic
description: Olympic organisers say the focus for the 2032 Olympic and Paralympic Games will now shift to ensuring the venues will be the perfect platform for athletes despite concerns over pressures facing the construction industry.

title: Regional SA council votes in favour of city-wide dry zone
description: Whyalla City Council will make an application to impose a city-wide dry zone after receiving anecdotal reports of an increase in alcohol-fuelled violence.

title: Its poison Gen Zs drinking habits are shifting
description: For a long time, drinking has been seen as a rite of passage for young Australians, but thats changing.

title: North Koreas Kim Jong Un condemns warship accident as criminal act
description: A new 5,000-tonne warship key to North Koreas naval advancement has been dropped on its side during its launching ceremony attended by leader Kim Jong Un.

title: Watt clears path for Woodside decision, rejecting green group concerns
description: The path has been cleared for a final decision on Woodsides proposal to extend the life of its North West Shelf gas project to 2070, with Environment Minister Murray Watt formally rejecting challenges by environment groups over the gas facility.

title: No love lost between Littleproud and Ley as they seek to reunite Coalition
description: While water devastated regional communities, senior Nationals were in Canberra divvying up the spoils of defeat.

title: Bondi killers satanic control claim not taken seriously by psychiatrist
description: Five experienced psychiatrists were called by the Westfield Bondi Junction inquest to provide their opinions on the treatment of Joel Cauchis mental health prior to the stabbing attack.

title: Expelled Labor MP breaks down in parliament as he defends alleged DV incident
description: In an emotional speech in parliament and speaking for the first time as an independent, Jimmy Sullivan addresses a recent alleged domestic incident saying it was not violent.
